SIMPLE: forthwith
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forthwith
<hw>Forth`with"</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?; see <er>With</er>)</pr>,
<pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Immediately; without delay;
directly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Immediately there fell from his eyes as it had been scales; and he
received sight <qex>forthwith</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Acts ix.
18.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>As soon as the thing required may
be done by reasonable exertion confined to that object.</def>
<rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forthy</ent>⟦br⟧
